[{"question":"I mean you guys are in the White House, aren\u0027t you?","answer":"Well, what I would say, first of all, Piers, is thank you so much for having me tonight.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":22,"aSentId":23},{"question":"Do you feel disappointed that there\u0027s been no greater inroad into those jobless figures?","answer":"I feel very disappointed that there hasn\u0027t been more inroad into those jobless figures.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":51,"aSentId":52},{"question":"If you\u0027re doing so well there, maybe you should be in the White House, have you thought of that?","answer":"Don\u0027t start something now, Piers.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":65,"aSentId":66},{"question":"I mean isn\u0027t it a bit frankly hypocritical to be throwing the toys out of the prime now and said the Democrats can\u0027t do it given how often the Republicans have done it?","answer":"Well, as you know, of course, Barack Obama voted against raising the debt ceiling when he was a senator and is now playing politics from the other side claiming that you\u0027re supposed to do this to give the president the money he wants.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":77,"aSentId":78},{"question":"I mean what percentage of blame, as we stand here today, should be apportioned to Republican decision making?","answer":"Well, again, you just asked about a number and I said of the cost of the Afghan war, I mean the whole Afghan war today cost $120 billion.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":101,"aSentId":102},{"question":"Why are you avoiding my question?","answer":"I\u0027m trying to give you a percentage of -- for instance the Afghan war, two-thirds of the cost there this year was put in by Obama.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":103,"aSentId":104},{"question":"Wasn\u0027t it?","answer":"Are you not remembering that Barack Obama campaigned for president on the idea that the Afghan war was the right war, that he was for all of that, and you want to explain --","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":110,"aSentId":111},{"question":"But you\u0027re asking for a partisan blame to be apportioned here, right?","answer":"No.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":114,"aSentId":115},{"question":"And so when you actually analyze exactly the percentage blame, and that\u0027s why I\u0027ve been trying to get you to put a percentage on it, it\u0027s just quite an interesting exercise, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Look, you want to argue why Medicare and Medicaid are going bankrupt, those were created by Democrats.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":119,"aSentId":120},{"question":"Do you want to go back to that and play partisan politics?","answer":"Why don\u0027t we --","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":121,"aSentId":122},{"question":"And that kind of partisan opinion is what is preventing any kind of sensible deal, a strategy being achieved, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"I started this conversation discussing that Bush spent too much money or allowed too much money to be spent during his presidency.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":135,"aSentId":136},{"question":"And the politicians should just sort this mess out, shouldn\u0027t they?","answer":"They should.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":153,"aSentId":154},{"question":"Mr. Mayor, how are you?","answer":"I\u0027m doing great.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":166,"aSentId":167},{"question":"I mean in your experience of these things, how much of what\u0027s going on right now in terms of this impasse between Republicans and Democrats is political and how much of it is actually about an ideology involving how to deal with the finances of this country?","answer":"Well, I can\u0027t say that I know the hearts and minds of the Congress people in our -- in the federal government.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":171,"aSentId":172},{"question":"Given that state of affairs, it\u0027s not in their interest politically to get him out of this hole, is it?","answer":"Well, I think it\u0027s going to be very clear, if people want to play brinkmanship with the debt ceiling and ultimately we are unable to pay our debts or worse unable to make payments to our military, to our Social Security recipients and others, what\u0027s going to happen is it\u0027s going to send a shockwave to our economy, it\u0027s going to drive interest rates up, it\u0027s going to cripple businesses all around our country.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":180,"aSentId":181},{"question":"It\u0027s the worst possible time for America to be in this position, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"It is.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":186,"aSentId":187},{"question":"And at the moment, they haven\u0027t flexed their muscles in the way that you just discussed involving Suez, but they could do, couldn\u0027t they?","answer":"Absolutely.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":207,"aSentId":208},{"question":"Everybody, really, in whatever way big or small has a bit of responsibility for the situation, doesn\u0027t it?","answer":"Well, to me, it\u0027s never about pointing blame.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":222,"aSentId":223},{"question":"If you were running the country right now and could talk to Americans in a way that perhaps woke them up to reality, what would you say?","answer":"Well, first of all, I have a lot of faith in the leader that we have in the White House.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":235,"aSentId":236},{"question":"In a simple way, what is the most effective way that you have seen to get them back to work, or the best plan that you\u0027ve heard?","answer":"First of all, this is the thing we have to get out of the habit of.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":298,"aSentId":299},{"question":"Would you welcome him doing that?","answer":"Look, you know, the governor, I always joke with him and I consider him a friend.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":324,"aSentId":325},{"question":"This is pretty serious stuff, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"It can be pretty serious stuff.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":381,"aSentId":382},{"question":"What are your key points of advice for people who look at this and are vaguely terrified?","answer":"One thing you need to remember is this: you don\u0027t want to wait or depend on this government to manage your life.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":393,"aSentId":394},{"question":"And is that the key lesson here, that when things look too good to be true, they always are too good to be true?","answer":"Well, that\u0027s exactly right.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":409,"aSentId":410},{"question":"Don\u0027t lots of people need to have some form of debt just to function?","answer":"Well, I think that\u0027s the misnomer.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":429,"aSentId":430},{"question":"Which, in your eyes, in your expert debt is dumb eyes, is normally the best way to get out of a crisis like this?","answer":"Well, I think there\u0027s certainly differences between a nation\u0027s debt and a personal debt.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":450,"aSentId":451},{"question":"Going to reveal the date of the wedding?","answer":"The date of the wedding.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":480,"aSentId":481},{"question":"Can I tell him?","answer":"Sure.","docId":"110713pmt","qSentId":482,"aSentId":483}]